Parliament, Monday, 18 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Arts and Culture will tomorrow be briefed by the Department of Arts and Culture on its entities. In particular, the forensic investigations into the Performing Arts Centre of the Free State, the National Arts Council, the South African Heritage Resources Agency, the National Library of South Africa, the National Film and Video Foundation, the South African Roadies Association and the Robben Island Museum. The department will also to speak about measures to deal with load shedding at its entities. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 19 February 2019
	Time: 09:30 
	Venue: SunSquare Cape Town Gardens, 10 Mill St, Gardens, Cape Town ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON ARTS AND CULTURE, MS XOLISWA TOM. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard (M.s)
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za Democracy is not an event that occurred in 1994. It is a process to which all of us can contribute by making our voices heard in Parliament, in the provincial legislatures and in broader society.Read more